The paper deals with multiclass and multilabel problems, which are typically studied in the machine learning community. The use of label embeddings is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) tasks, which suggests that cs.CL and cs.CV are likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of partial least squares, which is a statistical technique commonly used in data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on large-scale text datasets, which suggests that cs.IR (information retrieval) is another possible category. Overall, cs.LG (machine learning) is the most likely category, given the focus on multiclass and multilabel problems.
